08/04/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- EULEX and Kosovo police arrested on Thursday (April 7th) a Kosovo Serb suspected of committing war crimes in 1999. 
The suspected was identified as Zoran Kolic from Lipjan municipality. 
He is a senior official of the Independent Serb Liberal Party, which is part of the ruling coalition. 
"The charges relate to murder and inhumane treatment of civilians in Kosovo in May 1999," EULEX said in a statement. 
(Express, Kosova Sot - 08/04/11; Kohavision, RTK, Klan Kosova - 07/04/11)
